article.headline: Indiana St. 75, Drake 63
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Jake Odum's double-double led Indiana State to a 75-63 victory over Drake on Saturday. Odum, a freshman, had the third 20-point game of his career as well as 10 rebounds and a game-high four assists for the Sycamores (14-12, 9-6), who won their second straight game and equaled their Missouri Valley Conference victory total of last season. Carl RIchard scored 20 points for Indiana State, which shot 48.1 percent (25 of 52). Seth VanDeest had 17 points to pace the Bulldogs (11-15, 6-9), whose three-game winning streak ended. Ryan Wedel added 14 points plus a team-high six rebounds, and Ben Simons scored 10. Drake was outrebounded 34-32 and shot just 37.3 percent (19 of 51). The Sycamores, who swept the season series for the second straight year, led 35-30 at halftime and gradually pulled away.
